30:49.348 --> 30:51.304
Motive?
What kind of motive?
Her research.

30:51.392 --> 30:53.428
She thought we weren’t
giving her enough leeway.

30:53.519 --> 30:55.180
But we could have lost our grants.

30:55.271 --> 30:58.559
This whole place could go away without them.

30:58.649 --> 31:01.061
If she stole the cultures,
why did she sue?

31:01.152 --> 31:03.814
We didn’t have proof,
but I was sure it was her.

31:03.904 --> 31:06.361
- Okay. What went missing?
— It was a tropical virus.

31:06.449 --> 31:09.316
Uh, it’s found in Africa, Southeast Asia.

31:09.410 --> 31:11.321
- CHIKV.
- Yes.

31:11.412 --> 31:13.027
She killed someone with it?

31:13.122 --> 31:15.283
Well, apparently,
she changed it before she used it.

31:15.374 --> 31:20.164
If it’s mutated,
I don’t know any way to treat it.

31:23.799 --> 31:25.300
[ Device Beeps ]

31:25.384 --> 31:29.127
— How is Mr. Vaziri?
- His vitals actually seem more stable.

31:29.221 --> 31:31.633
Clearly, the herbs helped.
I came to apologize.

31:31.724 --> 31:36.388
No need. I understand that when
someone is blindly subservient
to institutional authority,

31:36.479 --> 31:38.765
theirjudgment is frequently compromised.

31:38.898 --> 31:41.355
That was
an eloquent insult.
lthoughtso.

31:41.442 --> 31:44.730
Did your department find any evidence
of CHIKV in Dr. Burke’s lab?

31:44.820 --> 31:47.232
Nothing. And according to witnesses,
she works day and night,

31:47.323 --> 31:50.190
so she wouldn’t have had time
to conduct experiments at another facility.

31:50.284 --> 31:53.367
So unless we find a way to tie CHIKV to her,
she can’t be arrested.

31:53.454 --> 31:55.035
Unfortunately, that’s the way it looks.

31:55.122 --> 31:56.498
Perhaps this will help.

31:56.582 --> 31:58.573
I thought you’d been over
the victim’s M.R.l.’s before.

31:58.667 --> 32:00.623
I took new scans because I saw this.

32:02.338 --> 32:04.795
— lt’s fractured.
— lt’s bowing outward.

32:04.882 --> 32:07.589
Which means the pressure
came from inside the bone.

32:07.718 --> 32:09.333
This break
wasn’t here before?
No.

32:09.428 --> 32:13.262
It occurred postmortem.
Now take a look at the most recent scans.

32:15.059 --> 32:17.050
That’s the site where Mia
was injected with the virus.

32:17.144 --> 32:19.556
You can see there’s a pocket
in the trabecular section of the bone.

32:19.647 --> 32:22.389
That’s where the pressure originated
that caused the fracture.

32:22.483 --> 32:25.316
- It looks like a small tumor.
— This isn’t CHIKV.

32:25.402 --> 32:27.313
There was something added to that injection.

32:27.404 --> 32:29.531
Something that’s still growing.

32:29.615 --> 32:32.106
I’m taking a slice for analysis.

32:32.201 --> 32:36.911
Perhaps we can determine what’s causing
this postmortem cellular reproduction.

32:42.503 --> 32:44.118
These are prokaryotes.

32:44.213 --> 32:48.126
That means the growth in the bone
isn’t viral. It’s a bacterial infection.

32:48.217 --> 32:50.754
So she was injected
with a virus and bacteria.

32:50.886 --> 32:55.220
The bacteria acted as a booster so that
the mutated virus would grow
even more quickly.

32:55.307 --> 32:57.798
— The botulinum toxin.
- Botulism?

32:57.893 --> 32:59.394
Yeah. Laboratory grade.

32:59.478 --> 33:01.184
Botulinum toxin’s
a Class “A” selected agent...

33:01.272 --> 33:02.933
strictly monitored through the C.D.C.

33:03.023 --> 33:05.765
Once we determine
the specific version of the toxin,

33:05.860 --> 33:08.272
we can prove that Dr. Burke
made it in her lab...

33:08.362 --> 33:10.899
and get the antiserum from her.

33:16.662 --> 33:19.278
Look, they’re bringing in Tessa Burke.
How soon till you get the results?

33:19.373 --> 33:23.082
Dr. Jacobs from the C.D.C.
is cross—checking the botulinum toxin...

33:23.169 --> 33:24.875
to see if it’s registered to her lab.

33:24.962 --> 33:26.327
Look, how’s Arastoo?

33:26.422 --> 33:28.378
The herbs are slowing progress,

33:28.465 --> 33:30.797
but I’m not sure how long he can hold out.

33:30.885 --> 33:33.797
Look, I’ll get what he needs from Burke.

33:35.014 --> 33:36.595
All right, look. She’s here.

33:36.682 --> 33:39.344
— Just get me that proof as soon as you can.
- Okay.

33:39.435 --> 33:42.677
This is absurd. I don’t have any antidote.

33:42.771 --> 33:45.934
Mia and l were on the same side.
I have no reason to kill her.

33:46.025 --> 33:48.687
You stole cultures from the last lab
that you worked at.

33:48.777 --> 33:52.645
How did you— That settlement was sealed.

33:53.616 --> 33:55.277
Thorne told you, didn’t he?

33:55.367 --> 33:58.109
— So you’re not denying this?
— I am, categorically.

33:58.204 --> 34:00.946
He accused me of stealing
so he could take all my notes.

34:01.040 --> 34:04.203
Simatech Biolab owned all my research,
and he wanted it for himself.

34:04.293 --> 34:06.705
Why didn’t you bring up Thorne before
when you talked to Dr. Sweets?

34:06.795 --> 34:08.786
Because I was under a court order,
which, apparently,

34:08.881 --> 34:11.372
means a hell of a lot more to me
than it does to Thorne.

34:11.467 --> 34:13.378
So you’re saying that
he has reason to kill Mia?

34:13.469 --> 34:16.961
I gave Mia everything I knew about
outbreaks, unethical lab practices.

34:17.097 --> 34:19.224
You’re talking
about Thorne now?
Yes.

34:19.308 --> 34:21.173
He would do anything to keep his grants.

34:21.268 --> 34:23.645
I told Mia. She was looking into him.

34:23.771 --> 34:27.810
He was about to lose 12 million
from the NIH. unless he came up
with something really big.

34:27.900 --> 34:29.561
You can check it out.

34:29.652 --> 34:32.018
If he was doing something unethical
and Mia found out about it—

34:32.154 --> 34:35.191
[Cell Phone Ringing]
he would do anything
to keep that quiet.

34:35.282 --> 34:37.659
— Booth.
— This is Dr. Jacobs with the C.D.C.

34:37.743 --> 34:40.780
The botulinum toxin
is registered to Simatech Labs.

34:40.871 --> 34:43.283
— lt’s run by—
- Yeah, Dr. Leonard Thorne. I know.

34:43.374 --> 34:45.456
So if someone stole
the culture two years ago—

34:45.542 --> 34:48.284
Impossible. Simatech
was only certified for the toxin this year.

34:48.379 --> 34:50.791
Okay. Thanks. Yeah, you can go now.

35:01.934 --> 35:06.894
This fall, we are gonna
drive through New England,

35:08.148 --> 35:10.981
see the leaves turn.

35:11.068 --> 35:15.311
I know this great inn that you would love.

35:17.700 --> 35:20.942
And you can teach me
how to make your abgoosht.

35:26.583 --> 35:28.539
I am so sorry that...

35:30.170 --> 35:32.832
I was too busy last weekend.

35:38.512 --> 35:40.377
[ Sniffles ]

35:45.060 --> 35:48.018
You are gonna get through this, Arastoo.

35:51.108 --> 35:53.224
You will.

36:06.290 --> 36:07.951
Do you need anything?

36:11.211 --> 36:13.998
You and Dr. Brennan already gave us...

36:14.089 --> 36:16.250
a little extra time.

36:17.760 --> 36:19.466
His vitals are dropping?

36:36.445 --> 36:39.278
You killed Mia Garrett because
she figured out you mutated the virus.

36:39.365 --> 36:41.356
I’ve already told you,
I don’t know Mia Garrett.

36:41.450 --> 36:43.111
You were gonna let it loose,
weren’t you, huh?

36:43.202 --> 36:46.865
You were gonna let the virus out.
Be the big hero.

36:46.955 --> 36:49.617
Come up with the cure so you’d get rich.

36:51.126 --> 36:54.163
I want a lawyer.
Yeah. A good man is gonna
die in a couple hours.

36:54.254 --> 36:56.666
I need the antidote.

36:56.757 --> 36:59.339
That’s it? Okay, let’s go
for a little walk, huh?

37:07.810 --> 37:09.926
— [ Knocking ]
- Bones!

37:10.020 --> 37:12.136
We shouldn’t do this.
We’re technically still on Iockdown.

37:12.231 --> 37:15.064
But if we don’t,
he’s just going to shoot out the lock.

37:15.192 --> 37:17.899
Open up.
[ Beeping ]

37:18.028 --> 37:19.643
[ Buzzing ]
Let’s go, huh?

37:19.780 --> 37:21.566
Call for help.
He can’t do this!
Sure, I can.

37:21.657 --> 37:23.864
I want you to see your handiwork.
Where’s Mia?

37:23.951 --> 37:27.068
— On the platform.
— On the platform, okay. Up here. Come on.

37:27.162 --> 37:30.245
— [Alarm Buzzing ]
- [ Device Beeps ]

37:30.332 --> 37:32.698
Take a look. Huh? Look!

37:32.793 --> 37:35.330
Is that what you wanted
to have happen to her, huh? Look at her.

37:35.421 --> 37:37.753
— Take a good look, Doc.
— You shouldn’t get him so close.

37:37.840 --> 37:40.377
Oh, right, right. We don’t want the doctor
to catch a cold here.

37:40.467 --> 37:43.004
What do you say we go
have a show—and—tell, huh? Come on.

37:43.095 --> 37:47.259
Security tapes at his lab show Mia coming
back to Simatech late at night.

37:47.349 --> 37:50.011
She was already sick.
She must have known what Thorne was up to.

37:50.102 --> 37:51.717
She wanted the antidote.

37:51.812 --> 37:54.770
So you just let her die and then sent her
to be destroyed with the animals.

37:54.857 --> 37:56.472
Let’s go take a look in here. Shall we?

37:56.567 --> 37:59.229
There’s your next victim.
He’s only got a couple hours to live.

37:59.319 --> 38:01.981
— We need the antidote.
— Please, he’s done nothing to you.

38:02.072 --> 38:05.280
If he tells us where the antidote is,
it’s an admission of guilt.

38:05.367 --> 38:08.279
— It’s over for you anyway.
— I’ve asked for my lawyer.
I know my rights.

38:08.370 --> 38:11.783
— These people are witnesses.
- No, Booth! Please.

38:11.874 --> 38:14.160
Please, his—

38:14.251 --> 38:19.666
His name is Arastoo Vaziri,
and he’s a good man,

38:19.756 --> 38:22.338
a generous man, and I...

38:25.220 --> 38:26.721
love him,

38:26.805 --> 38:29.046
and you know that this is not—

38:29.141 --> 38:32.224
He—He’s done nothing to deserve this.
You know that.

38:35.772 --> 38:37.433
What if this was someone you love?

38:37.524 --> 38:40.891
Would you let them die like this?

38:45.073 --> 38:48.611
[Whimpers]
Please help him.

38:55.667 --> 38:58.454
— I want my lawyer.
— Booth, that’s not going to help.

38:58.545 --> 39:00.661
I can talk to him.

39:00.756 --> 39:03.589
We couldn’t make an antiserum,

39:03.675 --> 39:07.714
but we were able to cultivate the virus
from the needle you stuck in Mia’s arm.

39:07.804 --> 39:12.264
— Bones, that’s not gonna work.
- I just want him to understand
what’s happening.

39:13.018 --> 39:14.303
Oh!

39:14.394 --> 39:15.895
[ Shouts ]

39:18.023 --> 39:20.685
- What have you done?
- I think it’s pretty clear what I’ve done.

39:20.776 --> 39:23.267
Perhaps now you’ll tell us
where the antiserum is.

